subtests.name: WebGL test #0: Two structs defined within non-overlapping scopes should be able to use the same name
WebGL test #1: A struct defined inside a scope overrides a struct defined in a outer scope with the same name
WebGL test #2: A struct can use the same name of another out-of-scope struct
WebGL test #3: A struct can't be defined with the same name as another struct defined in the same scope
WebGL test #4: Structs with appended underscored numbers don't cause link errors (ANGLE bug)
WebGL test #5: Variables of masked outer scope struct work with inner scope struct
